  "abstract": "The bud necrosis disease of groundnut (Arachis hypogaea\r\nL.) was first reported from India by Reddy et al.\r\n(1968). It was subsequently reported that bud necrosis\r\ndisease was caused by tomato spotted wilt virus (TSWV)\r\n(Ghanekar et al. 1979). Recent studies using advanced\r\nserological techniques have shown that the causal agent\r\nof bud necrosis disease is distinct from TSWV and it has\r\ntherefore been named bud necrosis virus (BNV)\r\n(Sreenivasulu et al. 1991, Reddy et al. in press). Hence\r\nBNV is considered to be a distinct member of the\r\ntospovirus group",
